    "body": "Hey @p4ck3t0, thanks for reporting the issue! We've revamped the ray executor backend in vLLM ([RFC](https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/issues/35848), [PR](https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/36836)). Please give it a try on nightly vLLM wheels with `VLLM_USE_RAY_V2_EXECUTOR_BACKEND=1` and setting `distributed_executor_backend=\"ray\"` as usual. The revamped ray executor backend no longer uses Ray compiled graph, so you shouldn't run into the issue. On a side note, the [original ray executor backend](https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/blob/main/vllm/v1/executor/ray_executor.py) using compiled graph is on deprecation path.",
